## What the test suite covers

| Area | Test class | Key assertions |
|---|---|---|
| **Happy path** | `TestOpenSavingsAccountHappyPath` | Returns `SavingsAccount`, status `ACTIVE`, correct customer link, balance preserved, account ID assigned, persisted via repo |
| **Minimum balance** | `TestMinimumBalanceEnforcement` | Accepts ≥ $100 (boundary included), rejects < $100, zero, negative values |
| **Tiered rates** | `TestTieredInterestRates` | All four tier boundaries plus mid-tier values; rate derived automatically (no caller input) |
| **Verification gate** | `TestCustomerVerificationGate` | Verified ✅, unverified ❌, suspended ❌, unknown customer ❌; failed requests leave repo untouched |
| **Idempotency** | `TestIdempotency` | Same object returned; account persisted exactly once; store queried on every call; different keys → different accounts; key stored on account; 10-repeat stress; mismatched payload still returns original; failed requests NOT cached |
| **Rate resolver unit** | `TestResolveInterestRate` | Pure function coverage of all boundaries and error path |
